The paper deals with information transmission by a swarm of mobile robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses coding theory and transmission delay, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of graphs and algorithms in the paper suggests that it could also belong to the categories of distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with the performance analysis of the proposed scheme, which could fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
